snippet.textDisplay:
Anti-SARS CoV2 Compounds from “Medicinal Plants”: Hiding in Plain Sight! https://lnkd.in/ee4DZPW
hashtag
#SARSCoV2
hashtag
#CoVID19
hashtag
#MedicinalPlants This 2020 study identified 3 plant compounds (from the Common Bean, Bayberry, and Bush Mint plants), very likely to be effective against SARS CoV2 and other coronaviruses. Interestingly, these have long been known in the pharmacognosy literature, as being active against a variety of microbes, including viruses. The Medical field has also known about these, and other, natural antivirals, for many years (2005 doi:10.1016/j.antiviral.2005.02.007 , 2007 doi:10.1016/j.antiviral.2007.03.003 , 2013 https://lnkd.in/eub3iJd , 2016 doi:10.3390/nu8020090 , 2017 https://lnkd.in/ekyqDrV). Another cheap, and widely available drug, chloroquine (used in malaria and autoimmune diseases, and is a derivative of quinine from Cinchona tree bark) is as active against SARS CoV2, as is the VERY EXPENSIVE (and, not yet available) Remdesivir (https://lnkd.in/eA3akav). Chloroquine is also anti-inflammatory, and is active against bacteria (2003 DOI: 10.1016/s1473-3099(03)00806-5). Chloroquine and the natural compounds cost pennies per dose, while Remdesivir is expected to be hundreds or thousands of dollars per dose.

First of all, Hitler started WW2, and nobody called it that back then, and Italy was aligned with Germany at the time.  Of course nobody in Italy panicked, they thought they were going to win it!
